Step-by-step with 10 students

mergeSort(&head, 1) — called on full list [A B C D E F G H I J]

Split → [A B C D E] and [F G H I J]

Recurse left → [A B C D E]

Split → [A B] and [C D E]

Recurse [A B] → [A] and [B]

Merge → mergeByGrade([A], [B]) → [A B]

Recurse [C D E] → [C] and [D E]

Recurse [D E] → [D] and [E]

Merge → mergeByGrade([D], [E]) → [D E]

Merge [C] and [D E] → [C D E]

Merge [A B] and [C D E] → [A B C D E]

Recurse right → [F G H I J]

Same splitting and merging → [F G H I J]

.............................
.............................
.............................

Final merge → mergeByGrade([A B C D E], [F G H I J]) → [A B C D E F G H I J]
